        "title": "How can i call the method from another class?",
        "body": "<p>Hi i am trying to solve the problem I am facing<\/p>\n<pre><code>public class exam {\n    public static void main(String[] args) {\n        test1 a = new test1();\n        \n       }\n    int zahl(int x, int y) {\n        int e;\n        if(x&gt;y) {\n            e=x-y;\n        }else {\n            e=y-x;\n        }\n        if(e==0) {\n            return 0;\n        }\n        int z=0;\n        int i=1;\n        while(i&lt;=e) {\n            z=z+i;\n            i++;\n        }\n        return z;\n    }\n\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n<p>what I want to do is to call the zahl method to the test1 class<\/p>\n<pre><code>public class test1{\n    private exam b;\n    \n    public void init() {\n        b = new exam();\n    }\n    void test() {\n        int result = b.zahl(2, 2);\n        assertEquals(1, result);\n    }\n\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n<p>this is what I have tried, but it returns nothing, even though it's supposed to show me error.<\/p>\n",
