        "creation_date": 1645107989,
        "body": "<p>You should probably be declaring your functions with the <code>public<\/code> tag i.e. <code>public void test()<\/code> if you intend to access them from other functions outside of that package. The usual <a href=\"https://www.oracle.com/java/technologies/javase/codeconventions-namingconventions.html\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">Class naming convention<\/a> in Java is with capital first letter, which makes your code more readable for you and others.<\/p>\n<p>For your question, I don't think you are actually invoking the <code>test()<\/code> method of the test1 class. If you want that method to get called every time, you could place it inside the default Constructor.<\/p>\n",
